One trick is to use water while wire wheeling. The water acts as a 
solvent, and helps to remove more of the rust (which will look like 
facial blackheads when burnished).


On Dec 5, 2003, at 8:47 AM, Tom and Thanh wrote:

>  shiny rust looks a lot better than the
> corroded oxidized look I hate so well!
